    "body": "AFAIK your best bet is to trace the transaction and see if the top-level call fails. But for that you'd probably need an archive node. In fact not being able to observe the status of a historical tx is why the status field was introduced in Byzantium as per the EIP [motivation](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-658.md).",
